{
  "id": "L19F",
  "title": "Visiting a Friend's Home",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you'll learn how to be a polite guest when visiting a French friend's home for the first time."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Salut",
        "meaning": "Hi"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19F_V01",
      "data": {
        "Une bouteille de vin": "A bottle of wine"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19F_V02",
      "data": {
        "Des fleurs": "Flowers"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "C'est pour toi",
        "meaning": "This is for you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19F_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "toi",
        "phonetic": "/twa/",
        "tip": "The 'oi' sound in French sounds like 'wa' in the English word 'water'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Quelle belle maison !",
        "meaning": "What a nice house!"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19F_S01",
      "title": "Arriving at Your Friend's Home",
      "setting": "You've just arrived at your friend Alex's home. The door opens.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet your friend",
          "chatbot_message": "Salut ! Entre, je t'en prie."
        },
        {
          "title": "Give your gift",
          "chatbot_message": "Merci beaucoup d'être venu(e)."
        },
        {
          "title": "Compliment their home",
          "chatbot_message": "Oh, merci, c'est très gentil ! Ça me fait plaisir."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great start! Now let's learn how to have some small talk. When offered something, 'Je veux bien...' is a polite way to accept."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Oui, je veux bien...",
        "meaning": "Yes, I'd like..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19F_V03",
      "data": {
        "Un café": "A coffee"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19F_V04",
      "data": {
        "De l'eau": "Water"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L19F_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "eau",
        "phonetic": "/o/",
        "tip": "This sounds just like the name of the letter 'o' in English."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Comment s'est passée ta semaine ?",
        "meaning": "How was your week?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Remember to use 'tu' and 'ta' when speaking with friends. It's the informal way to say 'you' and 'your'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Est-ce que je peux aider ?",
        "meaning": "Can I help?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19F_V05",
      "data": {
        "La cuisine": "The kitchen"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19F_S02",
      "title": "Having a Drink",
      "setting": "You are now in the living room with Alex.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Accept a drink and state your preference",
          "chatbot_message": "Merci ! Assieds-toi. Tu veux boire quelque chose ? Un café, de l'eau ?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask about their week",
          "chatbot_message": "D'accord. Je prépare ça."
        },
        {
          "title": "Offer to help in the kitchen",
          "chatbot_message": "Ma semaine était bonne, merci."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Excellent! Finally, let's learn how to politely end the evening and say goodbye."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L19F_V06",
      "data": {
        "Tard": "Late"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Il est tard",
        "meaning": "It is late"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Je dois partir",
        "meaning": "I have to go"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Merci pour la soirée",
        "meaning": "Thanks for the evening"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Au revoir",
        "meaning": "Goodbye"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L19F_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "À bientôt",
        "meaning": "See you soon"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L19F_S03",
      "title": "Time to Leave",
      "setting": "You've finished your drink and had a nice chat. It's time to head home.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "State that it's getting late",
          "chatbot_message": "Non, non, reste assis. C'est bon."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank your friend for the evening",
          "chatbot_message": "Oh, déjà ? D'accord."
        },
        {
          "title": "Say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "De rien. C'était sympa de te voir."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}